Movie: On the Occasion of Remembering the Turning Gate

Review: There's a profound stillness to this film. The camera lingers on every close up, refusing to release us from the moment. It's in these pauses, these instances of arrested longing, that we comprehend the roiling emotions under the surface of every glance. Unspoken yearning, articulated only in the slightest of winces, the shrug of a shoulder, the twitch of an eyebrow. To pull away would be to miss the seismic shift of emotion, communicated in the flicker of a smile.
